<div><div><h2>NTPC Q2 profit falls marginally, misses estimates</h2></div><div>power producer ntpc ltd reported a marginal fall in september-quarter profit on friday missing estimates as higher expenses weighed. profit came in at rs 2426 crore for the three months ended 30 september compared with rs 2439 crore a year earlier said the country s largest electric utility company by market capitalisation. analysts on average had expected a profit of rs 2578 crore according to ibes data from refinitiv. total expenses for the quarter rose 17.5% to rs 19851 crore. revenue from operations grew 13% to rs 22261 crore during the quarter.</div></div>